05/11/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- EU Home Affairs Commissioner Cecilia Malstrom arrived on Thursday (November 4th) for a two-day visit to support Greece's efforts in dealing with illegal immigrants crossing from Turkey. Her visit comes after the EU's border agency, FRONTEX, sent a team of border-control specialists to help Greek authorities, at Athens' request. Malstrom is expected to visit the Greek- Turkish border and a centre for asylum seekers. (DPA, EU website - 04/11/10)
